SIMPLE: oblige
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oblige
<hw>O*blige"</hw> <pr>(⟦osl⟧*bl⟦imac⟧j"; 277)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Obliged</conjf>
<pr>(⟦osl⟧*bl⟦imac⟧jd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Obliging</conjf> <pr>(⟦osl⟧*bl⟦imac⟧"j⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[OF. <ets>obligier</ets>, F. <ets>obliger</ets>, L.
<ets>obligare</ets>; <ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) +
<ets>ligare</ets> to bind. See <er>Ligament</er>, and cf.
<er>Obligate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To attach, as by a
bond.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had <qex>obliged</qex> all the senators and magistrates firmly
to himself.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To constrain by physical, moral, or legal force; to
put under obligation to do or forbear something.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>obliging</qex> power of the law is neither founded in,
nor to be measured by, the rewards and punishments annexed to it.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Religion <qex>obliges</qex> men to the practice of those virtues
which conduce to the preservation of our health.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To bind by some favor rendered; to place under a
debt; hence, to do a favor to; to please; to gratify; to
accommodate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus man, by his own strength, to heaven would soar,⟦br⟧
And would not be <qex>obliged</qex> to God for more.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The gates before it are brass, and the whole much
<qex>obliged</qex> to Pope Urban VIII.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall be more <qex>obliged</qex> to you than I can express.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. E. Montagu.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 991 --></p>

<p><ent>obligee</ent>⟦br⟧
